Cyber War


Over the past two decades, cyberspace has increasingly become a
battleground for nation states. Sophisticated malware, covert
operations, and attacks targeting critical infrastructure have
transformed the digital world into a new domain of conflict.

Several reports and investigations have suggested that some of the
earliest large-scale cyber operations were directed at sensitive
industrial systems and nuclear infrastructure, marking what many
analysts consider the beginning of modern cyber warfare.

Amid these developments, a DPRK party daily published commentary
accusing the United States of initiating this new era of conflict in
the digital domain, referring to it as the "prelude to cyber war."

Your task is to locate this declassified report and identify the
SERIAL number mentioned in the document header.

Flag format: HTB{serialnumber}

Category : OSINT
Author : Akash

Write-up
The challenge description talks about cyber warfare and mentions that a DPRK party daily accused the United States of initiating a new era of cyber conflict, referring to it as the “prelude to cyber war”.
Since the report is declassified, we can find declassified documents from CIA FOIA Electronic Reading Room,where many government documents are publicly available.

Website:
https://www.cia.gov/readingroom/search/site

Using the search bar on the site and searching for the keyword "prelude to cyber war" leads to a document named 
"DPRK PARTY DAILY BLAMES US FOR OPENING UP 'PRELUDE' TO 'CYBER WAR'"

Opening the PDF shows the declassified report. In the header section of the document, there is a field labeled SERIAL. The value listed there is:

KPR2015121060229029

Since the flag format is HTB{serialnumber}, 

the final flag is:
HTB{KPR2015121060229029}

